In dubbo-rpc/dubbo-rpc-api/src/main/java/org/apache/dubbo/rpc/protocol/AbstractProxyProtocol.java:
 > @@ -121,6 +121,13 @@ protected Result doInvoke(Invocation invocation) throws Throwable {                      throw getRpcException(type, url, invocation, e);                  }              } + +            @Override +            public void destroy() { +                super.destroy(); +                target.destroy(); +                invokers.remove(this); +            }  
I think it's unnecessary, because the AbstractProtocol's destroy method has the logic to remove invoker of invokers.
 
